<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1648">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.67/27.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-17">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my cablegrams of
                                February 13 and February 16, I now have the honor to submit to the
                                Department correspondence<note n="72" xml:id="d1648fn72">Not
                                    printed.</note>
                                <pb facs="1191" n="1075" xml:id="pg_1075"/> referring to the request
                                of the Syrians here for American protection, and also regarding the
                                execution of three Syrians by General Obregon on February 13,
                                1915.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">John R. Silliman.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>